This is a great game and a great concept. It is a bit buggy at times, but that doesn't affect too much when it comes to game play. The description says you can do "every trick there is" which is false. You can do almost every trick. Excluding ones such as, no comply, darkslide, primo slide, etc. But one would argue that those are beyond scope of the developers intentions. Which doesn't really take away from the game. Cons: I would advise that you don't change your Google Games name after installing this app. It messes with your score and there seems no way to fix it. I have copied over 300 runs and my score remains at zero. I would also suggest that you do not uninstall and reinstall the app as that has seemed to mess with my Parse.settings file. I reinstalled in hopes of it allowing me to change my name and now the file shows duplicate entries for copied runs. One set increases with every one and the other set stays the same. This is keeping me from getting the "200 runs" and "500 runs copied" achievements. I have also not been able to find away to get the "Grind Master" achievement. Contacting them on Insta has proven fruitless, as I received no response for about two weeks now.

It's a good alternative to true skate (if, like me, you've played ts to death). The tricks and physics are fairly realistic but the controls are somewhat disconnected and take a while to master, it also suffers from a fair few bugs. For the hefty price tag there just aren't enough spots to keep you entertained for longer than a few months. Great alternative if true skate is getting boring and you can justify spending the money.

content: Skater is a great game in some areas it deffinetly blows true skate out of the water the graphics are amazing the controls need a few changes but overall this is a well made game thats very fun to play but that being said there are some things i dont care for such as the pull and lock when you do grinds/slides ( I dont like it simply because when you try to gap over a ledge or rail and you accidently touch the wrong part of your screen it will pull you down to the rail even when thats not what your trying to do) it also calls alot of grinds 50/50s when i do smiths/feebles it almost always says 50/50 how can i possibly be doing a 50/50 with only 1 truck on the rail?? So yea in terms of grinds and slides true skates system is much better if skater used that system my rating would be five stars forsure but other than that skater is well worth the 6$ and i recommend trying it 9/10

content: This is a game with a lot of potential. It runs great, for about 20 minutes, then it begins to lag quite a bit. Even sooner if I have spotify playing in the background.  My Nexus 6 is running Android N Beta, I have no idea if that is a factor.  Beyond the bugs that are likely to be fixed in updates to come, the game is truly enjoyable. While the mechanics are not as free wheeling as True Skate, the game play feels much more natural that Touchgrind 2.  What really puts this game over are the aesthetics. The shoes, decks, and locations all work together beautifully. The colors are rich, which is give it another leg up on True Skate which always looks  a little washed out to me.  The community interaction aspects are awesome. In addition to the standard Leaderboard, you also have community designed challenges. You attempt to complete a line that someone else recorded. By completing (and creating) these challenges you are able to unlock new locations. I love this part, it brings back fond memories of the level challenges from THPS. The only thing I wish we had was a way to leave some sort of feed back on other peoples challenges.   All in all, I definitely recommend this one.
replyContent: Hey Geoff, we just updated to improve lag on some newer devices including your model. Let me know if it helps! Thanks for the other feedback, comments on challenges would be sweet too anything's possible in future..
